      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;motivation--&#34;&gt;Motivation üåå üå†&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recently I worked on a MeteorJS project. The live version of the app is hosted on &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.meteor.com/hosting&#34;&gt;Galaxy&lt;/a&gt; and there was no staging environment for this one. So we needed to deploy another instance of this app in a staging environment. The codebase was hosted on GitLab and we have a shared cluster of MongoDB in mLab. While we wanted to run the staging environment efficiently, we also wanted to make sure the deployment is as cost-effective as we can.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
